parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Actuator Pump Motor Assembly Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake actuator pump motor assembly can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle requires a longer stopping distance
there is an abnormal hissing sound coming from the front passenger side of the vehicle
the ABS warning light illuminates on the instrument control panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle requires a longer stopping distance
there is a fluid leak from underneath the vehicle
the brake pressure hose develops a small hole and brake fluid leaks out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries. It can also lead to a sense of fear and anxiety while driving.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly
often without warning
and may not respond to braking. The engine RPMs may increase rapidly
and the vehicle may move forward or backward unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: TPS failure can cause sudden acceleration, high idle speeds, and loss of control, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The engine idles at high speeds
the vehicle accelerates suddenly
or the throttle pedal sticks. The vehicle may not respond to braking
and the engine RPMs may increase rapidly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cruise control failure can cause sudden acceleration, loss of control, and accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly while the cruise control is engaged
and may not respond to braking. The engine RPMs may increase rapidly
and the vehicle may move forward or backward unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: High idle speed can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries. It can also lead to a sense of fear and anxiety while driving.
symptoms: The engine idles at high speeds
often without warning
and may not respond to braking. The vehicle may not respond to normal acceleration or deceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine mount can cause the engine to shift excessively, leading to damage to other components, and potentially causing the vehicle to stall or lose control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The engine mount bolts shear off
the engine shifts excessively
the vehicle is not drivable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel injectors can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires or explosions, posing a significant risk to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Fuel injectors start leaking or spraying gas
the engine compartment is flooded with gasoline.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to damage to the engine and potentially causing the vehicle to stall or lose control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle overheats
the thermostat fails
the fan clutch fails
the gasket fails
the water pump fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust system can cause rattling or loud noises, which can be a distraction to the driver and potentially lead to accidents. In extreme cases, it can also cause fires.
symptoms: The muffler and tailpipe fail
the exhaust has a continual rattle
the exhaust manifold cracks
causing fumes to enter the passenger compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause the vehicle to stall, which can lead to accidents, especially if it occurs at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls at all speeds
especially when hitting bumps or parked on hills
the engine shuts off at idle
shutting down motor/power steering/brakes
etc.
